{
  "thag3.10:0.1": "Verses of the Senior Monks 3.10 ",
  "thag3.10:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
  "thag3.10:0.3": "Chapter One ",
  "thag3.10:0.4": "Sāṭimattiya ",
  "thag3.10:1.1": "In the past you had faith, ",
  "thag3.10:1.2": "today you have none. ",
  "thag3.10:1.3": "What’s yours is yours alone—",
  "thag3.10:1.4": "I’ve done nothing wrong. ",
  "thag3.10:2.1": "Faith is impermanent, fickle: ",
  "thag3.10:2.2": "or so I have seen. ",
  "thag3.10:2.3": "Passions wax and wane: ",
  "thag3.10:2.4": "why would a sage waste away on that account? ",
  "thag3.10:3.1": "The meal of a sage is cooked ",
  "thag3.10:3.2": "bit by bit in this family or that. ",
  "thag3.10:3.3": "I’ll walk for alms, ",
  "thag3.10:3.4": "for my legs are strong. "
}